text.section:
Subject to the authority of the Board, jurisdiction over procurement is as follows:
the State Treasurer may engage in or control procurement of banking and financial services, insurance, and insurance services, as provided in Division I of this article and Article VI, § 3 of the Maryland Constitution;
the Department of Budget and Management may control procurement of:
services by a unit, subject to any limitation in this Division II; and
leases of motor vehicles, as provided in Title 3, Subtitle 5 of this article;
the Department of General Services may engage in or control procurement of:
leases of real property, including leases under Title 4, Subtitle 3 of this article;
supplies, including supplies under Title 4, Subtitle 3 of this article, but excluding insurance, information processing equipment, and motor vehicle leases;
construction, including construction under Title 4, Subtitle 4 of this article;
construction related services, including those under Title 4, Subtitle 4 of this article; and
architectural or engineering services under Title 13, Subtitle 3 of this article;
the Department of Transportation and the Maryland Transportation Authority, without the approval of any of the other primary procurement units, may engage in the procurement of:
construction that is related to transportation, as provided in the Transportation Article;
construction related services that are related to transportation, as provided in the Transportation Article;
architectural or engineering services that are related to transportation, under Title 13, Subtitle 3 of this article;
rolling stock and other property peculiar to the operation of a transit system, as provided in § 7-403 of the Transportation Article;
supplies for aeronautics related activities, including motor vehicles and information processing supplies, but excluding:
supplies funded by the proceeds from State general obligation bonds; and
insurance; and
services for aeronautics related activities, including information processing services, but excluding banking and financial services under the authority of the State Treasurer under item (1) of this subsection;
the Maryland Port Commission, without the approval of any of the other primary procurement units, may engage in the procurement of:
supplies for port related activities, including motor vehicles and information processing supplies, but excluding:
supplies funded by the proceeds from State general obligation bonds; and
insurance;
services for port related activities, including information processing services, but excluding banking and financial services under the authority of the State Treasurer under item (1) of this subsection;
construction and construction related services for a port facility as defined in § 6-101(e) of the Transportation Article;
port related architectural and engineering services under Title 13, Subtitle 3 of this article; and
leases of real property for port related activities unless the lease payments are from the General Fund of the State;
the Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services may, without the approval of any of the other primary procurement units:
engage in the procurement of construction and construction related services for State correctional facilities; and
engage in the procurement of supplies, materials, and equipment in support of construction and construction related services for State correctional facilities in accordance with this Division II and Title 2 and Title 10, Subtitle 1 of the Correctional Services Article; and
the Department of Information Technology may control procurement of:
information processing equipment and associated services, as provided in Title 3A, Subtitle 3 of this article; and
telecommunication equipment, systems, or services, as provided in Title 3A, Subtitle 4 of this article.
